Just TWO DAYS LEFT!!!!
Today @vcs_art_class on Instagram live, we took a look at portrait artist Kehinde Wiley. You may have seen that Wiley recently painted Barrack Obamaâ€™s official portrait. Wiley paints large, beautiful photorealistic portraits of African Americans using styles and symbols that rewrite history, and call into question the ways that black people are represented throughout history and in contemporary culture. Today in art class, we learned to draw a simple portrait, and create a patterned background that is a signature of Wileyâ€™s paintings. Swipe to see examples of Wileyâ€™s artwork as well as steps to drawing a human face, and my drawing example. See you tomorrow amazing artists! Ms. Difranco ğŸ’š

post_text:
#mentalhealthsupport for Mercer County
The ISP is the Immediate Services Program funded by FEMA/SAMHSA to provide mental health supports in the aftermath of disaster. The ISP has been extended until the RSP, Regular Services Program is fully implemented. Catholic Charities, Diocese of Trenton is one of 4 agencies to provide psychoeducation, stabilization and support services related to the impact of COVID-19. Additionally, there are drop-in groups and other services provided by the Mental Health Association.

The Regular Services Program will begin soon with additional agencies providing services to Mercer County residents. The attached flyer is for the Catholic Charities ISP services which are available in English and Spanish.

post_text:
CONGRATULATIONS
Attorney- in-Charge âœ¨Fabiana Pierre-Louisâœ¨

If the state Senate confirms the nomination, Pierre-Louis will be the first Black woman to ever sit on this court. @essence
Fabiana Pierre-Louis and The United States Attorneyâ€™s Office for the District of New Jersey implemented The Project LEAD program at Village Charter School for two years. The program enabled our fifth grader scholars to learn about state vs. federal laws and the criminal justice system. As a result, students completed the program with a better understanding of these laws and careers in the legal field. The program culminated with a trip to the Mercer County Court House, where students held a mock trial.
#ittakesavillage #congratulations #FabianaPierreLouis
